!! Image basic
The `image-basic` macro is used to simply display an image with the desired size, aligining, caption and tooltip.

!! Syntax

```
<<image-basic img width:"30%" align:"left"  caption:"" tooltip:"">>
```

!! Content and attributes
|!Attributes |!Type |!Description |
|img ||the URL of the image, or the title of an image tiddler |
|width |optional|the width of the image, height is set automatically, default value is 30%|
|align |optional|`left`, `right`, `center`, alignment of image, default is `left`|
|caption |optional|the image caption appears below image|
|tooltip |optional|the tooltip to be displayed over the image|

!! Example
```
<<image-basic 
  img:"myfig.png" 
  width:"18rem" 
  align:"center" 
  caption:"Fig 1. This is a sample image" 
  tooltip:"My basic image">>
```

